    thinking: "**Designing the Topbar**\n\nI\'m focusing now on making the topbar incredibly clean and modern. I\'m prioritizing rounded-full elements, subtle shading around borders, and very professional spacing. I\'m also ensuring the logo aligns with the Bento Grid style, potentially incorporating a small logo icon block if it fits the design. I\'ve encountered a small snag, but I\'ll continue to refine.\n\n\n**Elevating the Dashboard**\n\nI\'m now exploring how to translate the existing `/src/views/Dashboard.tsx` into a compelling Bento Grid. The objective is to arrange dashboard cards in visually distinct bento-style elements, with varying span sizes. I\'m imagining a widescreen \"Greeting Header\" with a hero gradient (Indigo to Slate) to highlight school status, date, active lessons, and stats in a single, cohesive bento header. I\'m evaluating how the main feature card could be represented.\n\n\n**Refining Dashboard Cards**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the Dashboard\'s \"Aktueller Unterricht\" card. I\'m focusing on the visual hierarchy, making sure key information like the lesson title, class, and room are immediately noticeable. The \"Bento Glow\" effect is a must-have. I\'m experimenting with subtle background gradients and shadows to create depth and emphasis.\n\n\n**Perfecting the Bento Grid**\n\nI\'m now reorganizing the Dashboard grid to be a perfect bento layout. I\'m focusing on the \"Temperatur/Infobox\" and \"Stunden\" elements, envisioning them as compact, aesthetically pleasing mini squares. Specifically, I\'m aiming for a clean 1x1 bento card with an emerald accent for \"Temperatur und Wetter\", and the same for Unterrichtsstunden. The Bento Grid will feel active with those changes.\n\n\n"
